This category is about packaging Emacs extension, or about utilities that can automate searching, downloading and installing extensions.

== Implementations ==

=== Repositories ===

* [[ELPA]] -- Emacs Lisp Package Archive.  Package repository used by [[Package]].  Install archives.
** [[MELPA]] -- built automatically on their server from upstream sources using recipes
** [[Marmalade]] -- users upload their own packages
* [[DELPS]] -- Distributed Emacs Lisp Package System used by [[Epackage]].  Install [[Git]] packaged repositories.
* EmacsLispList -- A long list of packages with summaries and links.  List packages using [http://www.damtp.cam.ac.uk/user/sje30/emacs/ell.el ell.el]
* [[Emacsmirror]] -- Collects packages and distributes them as [[Git]] repositories.  List packages using [[Epkg]].

=== Package Managers ===

* AutoInstall
* [[el-get]]
* [http://repo.or.cz/w/elinstall.git elinstall]
* [[Epackage]]
* [http://www.iro.umontreal.ca/~monnier/elisp/install.el install]
* [http://www.emacswiki.org/emacs/install-elisp.el install-elisp]
* [http://www.jemarch.net/jempkg.html jem-pkg]
* [https://launchpad.net/pases pases]
* [http://github.com/eggcaker/pelm pelm]
* [http://gmarceau.qc.ca/plugin.el plugin]
* [http://www.emacswiki.org/emacs/UsePackage use-package]
* [http://www.xemacs.org/Documentation/packageGuide.html XEmacs package manager]

=== Related Tools ===

* [http://www.emacswiki.org/emacs/EmacsLispList ell.el] -- Browse and download files from [http://www.emacswiki.org/emacs/WikifiedEmacsLispList Emacs Lips List].

== Discussions ==

* [http://lists.nongnu.org/mailman/listinfo/emacs-pms-dev Emacs Package Managers] -- Dedicated mailing list.
* RationalElispPackaging -- Discussion and presentations of existing implementation.
* [http://stackoverflow.com/questions/454259 What do you expect from a package manager for Emacs] -- Opinions of various users.
